<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Research Portal Help</title>
    <%= render "help/common_style" %>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="header-bar">
      <h1>Research Portal Help</h1>
      <%= link_to "Back to Projects", projects_path, class: "btn-back" %>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
      <h2>Welcome to the Research Opportunities Portal!</h2>
      <p>This guide helps you navigate the portal and find research projects.</p>

      <h2>Viewing Projects</h2>
      <p>
        The main page displays a list of available research projects. Each
        project card shows key information:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Project Title:</strong>
          The name of the research project.</li>
        <li><strong>Research Area:</strong>
          The field(s) the project falls under.</li>
        <li><strong>Dates:</strong>
          Start and End dates (if specified).</li>
        <li><strong>Positions:</strong>
          Number of students needed.</li>
        <li><strong>Description:</strong>
          A brief overview of the research.</li>
        <li><strong>Faculty:</strong>
          The professor(s) leading the project.</li>
        <li><strong>Contact:</strong>
          Email address(es) for the faculty or admin contact.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Scroll through the page to see all active projects. Projects might have
        different availability types like "One semester", "Date range", or
        "Anytime".
      </p>
      <%# <div class="screenshot-placeholder">[ Placeholder: Screenshot of a project card ]</div> %>

      <h2>Searching for Projects</h2>
      <p>
        Use the search bar at the top of the projects list to find specific
        opportunities. You can search by:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Project Title</li>
        <li>Research Area</li>
        <li>Faculty Name or Email</li>
        <li>Keywords in the description (may vary based on implementation)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Enter your search term and click the "Search" button. To see all
        projects again, click the "Reset" button.
      </p>
      <%# <div class="screenshot-placeholder">[ Placeholder: Screenshot of the search bar ]</div> %>

      <h2>Contacting Faculty</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about a specific project, you can use the contact
        email address listed on the project card to reach out directly to the
        faculty member or admin associated with it.
      </p>

      <h2>Applying for Projects</h2>
      <p>
        To apply for projects, you need to be signed in as a student. If you
        are not signed in, you will see a prompt to sign in using your Google
        account.
      </p>
      <%= button_to "Sign in with Google",
      user_google_oauth2_omniauth_authorize_path,
      method: :post,
      class: "btn btn-primary mt-2",
      data: {
        turbo: false,
      } %>
      <p class="mt-3">
        If you are a student, please sign in and refer to the Student Help
        section for instructions on how to apply.
      </p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
